<h3 id="ip-mode">IP/Ethernet Mode Integrations (410IP)</h3>

If your PACS communicates with the ENGAGE Gateway over IP/Ethernet, you will need to update your code to handle the new `gwe2` model identifier.

<Panel type="warning" title="Key Point">
  The API changes described below are the **ONLY** changes required for IP-mode
  integrations. All other features, functionality, and API behaviors remain
  identical between GWE and GWE2.
</Panel>

#### API Endpoint Changes

The following API endpoints include the model type in the URL path. Your code must be updated to use `gwe2` when working with GWE2 devices:

| Operation              | GWE Endpoint                                            | GWE2 Endpoint                                            |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| Get Device Defaults    | `GET /engage/sites/{siteReference}/devicedefaults/gwe`  | `GET /engage/sites/{siteReference}/devicedefaults/gwe2`  |
| Set Device Defaults    | `POST /engage/sites/{siteReference}/devicedefaults/gwe` | `POST /engage/sites/{siteReference}/devicedefaults/gwe2` |
| Update Device Defaults | `PUT /engage/sites/{siteReference}/devicedefaults/gwe`  | `PUT /engage/sites/{siteReference}/devicedefaults/gwe2`  |
| Get Firmware           | `GET /engage/firmware/gwe`                              | `GET /engage/firmware/gwe2`                              |

&nbsp;

#### API Response Changes

The following API responses will return a different model identifier (`gwe2` instead of `gwe`) when working with GWE2 devices:

##### GET /engage/devices/site/&#123;siteReference&#125;

